                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-11T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 11, 1929—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>560. My 557, July 11, 3 p.m.<note n="76" xml:id="d92fn76">See footnote 75, <ref
                            target="#pg_198">p. 198</ref>.</note> Following from American Consul at
                    Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 11, 11 a.m. Chinese authorities have discharged Soviet general
                            manager of railway, Soviet assistant manager and all Russian heads of
                            departments. Fan Chi-kuan, member of board and also Chinese assistant
                            manager, has taken over chargé as general manager.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
